docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:327:## 8. Model tiers & admin configuration
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:329:Four tiers: `free`, `cheap`, `balanced`, `expensive`. Default `balanced`. Per-user setting in `profile.json`. Per-`(tier, step_kind)` model in PG. Both admin-editable.
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:349:Initial values; admin edits each cell independently.
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:361:### 8.3 Admin panel: `/admin/models`
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:363:A 4 × 7 grid. Each cell: model dropdown (populated from cached `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models`) + optional fallback dropdown. Save → UPSERT row. The `updated_by` column captures the admin user. A toggle at the top of the page disables the `free` tier globally (useful if OpenRouter free pool degrades).
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:365:### 8.4 Admin panel: `/admin/users` extension
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:402:| `budget_exhausted` | (When daily caps ship) projected next-step cost exceeds remaining headroom. No-op for `free` and during initial pilot. | Daily cron at user-TZ rollover flips back to `running` |
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:403:| `manual` | User or admin click | Manual resume click |
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:421:- Admin cancels via `/admin/jobs`
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:450:Idempotent admin script:
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-30-step-queue-execution-redesign-design.md:464:soofke (or admin via `/admin/jobs`) clicks "Full Report" in `/controls`. Dispatcher creates 1 `JobEntity` + 10 `TickerWorkItem` + 70 `StepWorkItem` rows. Executor processes them. Progress visible per-step in the UI. Completes within 1–2 days at `balanced` tier (target $0.50/user/day envelope).
