docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-10-admin-controls.md:1:# Admin Controls Implementation Plan
docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-10-admin-controls.md:5:**Goal:** Build a full admin control panel — per-user restriction levels (readonly/blocked/suspended), system-wide lock, broadcast messages, force-logout via tokenVersion, kill active jobs, rate-limit override, plus proxy-level enforcement that blocks Telegram and scheduled crons too.
docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-10-admin-controls.md:7:**Architecture:** Control state lives in `users/{userId}/control.json` (per-user) and `data/system-control.json` (system-wide). The LLM proxy is the universal enforcement choke point — blocked users' agent sessions die at the first LLM call, covering Telegram and cron triggers automatically. The HTTP API enforces at `jobs.ts` (fast-fail before trigger file is written) and `authMiddleware` (tokenVersion for force-logout). The frontend polls `GET /api/me/control` and renders the appropriate UI state: normal, info banner, warning banner, or full-screen suspension page.
