docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-10-admin-controls.md:342:The JWT payload gets a `tokenVersion: number` field. On every authenticated request, authMiddleware reads the user's `auth.json` to compare. Force-logout = increment `auth.json`'s tokenVersion; all existing JWTs for that user instantly fail.
docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-10-admin-controls.md:344:Backward compat: existing tokens without `tokenVersion` field treat it as 0, which matches `auth.json` default of 0 — so existing sessions survive the deploy.
